</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We will also act on any other business that may properly come before the meeting, although, as of the date
of this proxy statement, we have not received notice of any other matters that may be properly presented. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Your vote is very important
regardless of how many shares of KCG Holdings, Inc. (the &#147;Company&#148; or &#147;KCG&#148;) you own. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A Notice of
Internet Availability of Proxy Materials (the &#147;Notice&#148;) is being mailed on March&nbsp;31, 2017 to all of our stockholders who have not requested a paper or electronic copy of our proxy materials, and the proxy materials relating to the
Annual Meeting will first be made available on or about that date. The Notice includes instructions on how to access this Proxy Statement (the &#147;Proxy Statement&#148;) and the 2016 Annual Report to Stockholders and how to vote online.
Stockholders who do not receive the Notice will continue to receive either a paper or an electronic copy of our proxy materials, which will be sent on or about March&nbsp;31, 2017. Whether or not you plan to attend the Annual Meeting, your shares
should be represented and voted. After reading this Proxy Statement and the instructions on the Notice or proxy card, please submit your proxy by telephone or through the Internet or by mail as indicated on the accompanying Notice or proxy card. If
voting by mail, please complete, sign, date and return the paper proxy card in the postage-paid envelope provided or return it to Vote Processing, c/o Broadridge, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York 11717. You may revoke your proxy at any time
before its exercise by: (i)&nbsp;attending and voting in person at the Annual Meeting; (ii)&nbsp;giving notice of revocation of the proxy at the Annual Meeting; (iii)&nbsp;submitting a proxy relating to the same shares and matters to be considered
at the Annual Meeting by telephone, through the Internet or by submitting a paper proxy card on a later date than the proxy previously submitted; or (iv)&nbsp;delivering a written notice of revocation to the Corporate Secretary of KCG. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sincerely, </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SUMMARY INFORMATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To assist you in reviewing the proposals, including the election of directors, the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> advisory vote on executive compensation and the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> advisory vote on the frequency of the advisory vote on executive compensation, the following
summarizes information about our 2016 financial performance, our corporate governance structure and our compensation program. This summary does not contain all of the information that you should consider when deciding how to vote your shares. You
should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting. See &#147;Annual Meeting Information&#148; beginning on page 59 for details on the voting process and how to attend the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>BUSINESS HIGHLIGHTS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">KCG combines advanced technology with specialized client service across market making, agency execution and trading venues, and also engages in principal trading via exchange-based electronic market
making. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>2016 Business results: </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR BGCOLOR="#dff6fb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Board Independence&nbsp;&amp; Leadership</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Corporate Governance Structure and
Practices</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Independent, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman: Charles E. Haldeman, Jr.</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Independent director nominees: 10 of 11</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Added four new independent directors, each with financial expertise and
relevant industry knowledge</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seven of the 11 director nominees have been elected to the Board since
the closing of the Mergers (as defined below)</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Four standing Board committees</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nine Board meetings and 21 committee meetings in 2016</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No staggered Board</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Majority voting in uncontested director elections, with director
resignation policy</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual Board self-evaluation and committee evaluations</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Directors required to own stock having a value of $240,000 within five
years of joining the Board</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Expanded former Risk Committee to Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee
to enhance focus on technology related governance matters</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>COMPENSATION HIGHLIGHTS (see pages <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">26-36)</FONT> </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Executive Compensation Program</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> for perquisites</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No single-trigger change in control benefits</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> on severance payments</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recoupment of cash incentive and equity awards from executive officers in the event of certain financial statement restatements and other events</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8px">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual reviews of our executive compensation program by our
Compensation Committee</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No stock options granted with an exercise price below market</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
repricing of underwater stock options</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:4.00em; text-indent:-1.50em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No excessive perquisites or benefits</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="95%"></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#dff6fb" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="tx129066_1"></A><A NAME="toc322410_1"></A>PROPOSAL 1&#151;ELECTION OF
DIRECTORS</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You are being asked to elect the 11 nominees named in this Proxy Statement to serve on
the Board of Directors of KCG Holdings, Inc. (which we refer to as &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; the &#147;Company&#148; or &#147;KCG&#148;) until the 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and until their successors have been duly elected and
qualified, or until their earlier death, resignation or removal. Each nominee currently serves on our Board of Directors (which we refer to as the &#147;Board of Directors&#148; or the &#147;Board&#148;), including Peter R. Fisher, Colin Smith,
Heather E. Tookes and Adrian Weller, who were elected to the Board on January&nbsp;18, 2017. Rene M. Kern and John C. (Hans) Morris are not seeking <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> to the Board, and their respective terms will
expire upon the election of directors at the Annual Meeting, at which time the Board will be reduced to 11 members. We thank Messrs. Kern and Morris for their many contributions to the Board and to the Company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We do not know of any reason why any nominee named in this Proxy Statement would be unable to serve as a director if
elected. If any nominee is unable to serve, the shares represented by all valid proxies will be voted for the election of such other person as may be nominated in accordance with our Second Amended and Restated
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws</FONT> (the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;By-Laws&#148;),</FONT> as described below. Proxies cannot be voted for a greater number of persons than the number of nominees named in this Proxy Statement.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>The Board unanimously recommends you vote &#147;<U>FOR</U>&#148; each of the nominees described below. </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_2"></A>Nominees for Election as Directors </B></FONT></P>

the Board the nomination of each nominee named below. Our Board believes that all of the following nominees meet the criteria described below with diversity and depth of experience that enable them to effectively oversee management of the Company.
No nominee for director has a family relationship with any nominee for director or executive officer of the Company. Information relating to each nominee for election as director, including his or her period of service as a member of the Board of
Directors, principal occupation, specific experience, other biographical material and qualifications is described below: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Independent</B></FONT></P>

2012 through the closing of the Mergers. Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt has more than 38 years of audit experience and spent over 29 years as a partner with KPMG LLP (&#147;KPMG&#148;), primarily in the financial services industry, before retiring in September
2011. During his tenure at KPMG, Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt served as the Area Professional Practice Partner for KPMG&#146;s Northeast Area and served on the firm&#146;s National Professional Practice Committee and the Area Leadership Team. He most recently
served as the Global Lead Audit Partner for Bank of New York Mellon. Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt previously was the partner in charge of Risk Management/Professional Practice for KPMG&#146;s Western Area and served in KPMG&#146;s New York, San Francisco and
Providence/Boston Office practices during his career. He was also a Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) Reviewing Partner, and has served as a college relations partner and a KPMG national training instructor. Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt is a
member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants. He received a B.S. in Accounting from Bryant University (formerly Bryant College) in 1973 and currently serves as a Trustee. Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt previously served as past Chairman of The
Alumni Association and Member of the Accounting Department Advisory Board for Bryant University.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" align="left">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt&#146;s qualifications to serve on the Board of Directors include his substantial auditing and accounting background as a
certified public accountant, extensive experience with, and knowledge of, the financial services industry, his strong background regarding SEC financial reporting and his prior service as lead partner to numerous large diversified financial services
clients and other large SEC issuers.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ADRIAN WELLER</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Independent</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>KCG Director since 2017</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Age 46</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Director of KCG, Dr.&nbsp;Weller is a Senior Research Fellow in the Machine
Learning Group at the University of Cambridge, a Faculty Fellow at the Alan Turing Institute and an Executive Fellow at the Leverhulme Centre for the Future of Intelligence. He is a leading authority on artificial intelligence, its commercial
applications and how it may be used to benefit society. Previously, Dr.&nbsp;Weller held senior roles in fixed income trading at Goldman Sachs, Salomon Brothers and Citadel. He received B.A. and M.A. degrees in mathematics from Trinity College,
University of Cambridge, and an M.S. and PhD in computer science from Columbia University.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dr.&nbsp;Weller&#146;s qualifications to serve on the Board of Directors include his extensive experience in trading and investing and his expertise in artificial intelligence.</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_3"></A>Term </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Each director elected will hold office until the 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and until the director&#146;s
successor is duly elected or qualified, or until the director&#146;s earlier death, resignation or removal. Any director may resign at any time upon written notice to the Company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_4"></A>Majority Voting Standard for Election of Directors </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws,</FONT> in an uncontested election of directors, each director will be elected if a majority of the votes cast at any meeting at which a quorum is
present are for the election of the director. For these purposes, votes cast include directions to withhold authority and exclude abstentions with respect to the director&#146;s election. In the event of a contested election, in which the number of
candidates for election as directors exceeds the number of directors to be elected, each director will be elected by the vote of a plurality of the votes cast at any meeting at which a quorum is present. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If a nominee for director who is an incumbent director is not elected and no successor has been elected at the meeting,
the director will promptly tender his or her resignation to the Board. The N&amp;CG Committee will recommend to the Board whether to accept the tendered resignation or whether other action should be taken. The Board will then act on the tendered
resignation, taking into account the N&amp;CG Committee recommendation, and publicly disclose its decision within 90 days from the date of certification of election results. The Board and N&amp;CG Committee, in making such a determination and
recommendation, may consider any factors or information as they considered appropriate and relevant. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If the
director&#146;s resignation is not accepted by the Board, the director will serve until the next annual meeting and until his or her successor is duly elected, or until his or her subsequent voluntary early resignation or removal. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-6-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_5"></A>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_6"></A>BOARD LEADERSHIP </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_7"></A>Our Board Leadership Structure </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Board is currently led by an independent director serving as <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT>
Chairman, Mr.&nbsp;Haldeman. The Board has determined that having an independent director serve as the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board is in the best interests of stockholders because it allows the
Chairman to focus on the effectiveness and independence of the Board while the CEO focuses on executing the Company&#146;s strategy and managing the Company&#146;s operations and performance. As the independent,
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman, Mr.&nbsp;Haldeman presides over meetings of the stockholders and the Board of Directors at which he is present. At this time, the Board believes this structure is an important mechanism
for enhancing the governance practices of the Board, ensuring that independent and open discussions occur amongst independent directors and between directors and management and facilitating a leadership position within the Board. The Board maintains
the authority at all times to modify this structure if necessary when doing so would be in KCG&#146;s best interests. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Board believes that the current leadership structure is efficient and in the best interests of the Company for the following reasons: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Having a separate Chairman of the Board and CEO allows the Company to strengthen its corporate governance practices. Mr.&nbsp;Coleman, as CEO, is
able to focus on KCG&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">day-to-day</FONT></FONT> management and operations and the execution of KCG strategies, while Mr.&nbsp;Haldeman is able to focus on Board matters and the
relationship of and interaction between the Board and management; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The independent, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board provides valuable assistance to the Board and the CEO.
That assistance entails: (1)&nbsp;ensuring that independent and open discussions occur amongst Board members, including through quarterly executive sessions of the Board; (2)&nbsp;assuming a leadership role in facilitating discussion or addressing
issues regarding governance issues, as appropriate, and providing feedback and strategic guidance to the Board; (3)&nbsp;serving as a liaison among and between independent directors and the CEO with respect to issues not readily or easily discussed
in a formal setting; (4)&nbsp;being a strategic advisor, mentor and business partner to the CEO and helping him to achieve the strategic goals of KCG; and (5)&nbsp;maintaining regular interaction with senior management between Board meetings.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_8"></A>DIRECTOR QUALIFICATIONS AND INDEPENDENCE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_9"></A>Director Qualifications </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The N&amp;CG Committee&#146;s principal responsibilities are to assist the Board in reviewing and identifying individuals qualified to become Board members, consistent with criteria approved by the Board,
and to recommend to the Board nominees for directors for the next annual meeting of stockholders and to fill vacancies on the Board. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our N&amp;CG Committee has established in its charter criteria to be considered in evaluating an individual for nomination to the Board. Director nominees should: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Be of the highest ethical character and share our values; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Generally have experience at a strategy/policy setting level or have high-level managerial experience in a relatively complex organization;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In some cases be widely recognized as leaders in the fields of financial services or technology; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Have relevant expertise and experience and be able to offer advice and guidance to our CEO based on that expertise and experience; and
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-7-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Have the ability to exercise sound business judgment, work effectively with others and have sufficient time to devote to our affairs.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We also seek to select a diverse group of directors for nomination to the Board, with
diversity reflecting a range of talents, ages, professional skills, background and experience. There is no formal process for implementing this policy, but diversity is considered by the Board in determining overall Board composition. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Additionally, our Corporate Governance Guidelines (a copy of which may be found on our website at <U>www.kcg.com</U> in
the &#147;Corporate Governance&#148; section of &#147;Investors&#148;) set forth a list of factors that, absent a waiver by a majority of the Board, will disqualify an individual from service on our Board. These factors require that a director
<B>not</B>: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Be an employee or director of a company in significant competition with the Company; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Be an employee or director of a major or potentially major customer, supplier, contractor, counselor or consultant of the Company;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Have been an employee of the Company or its subsidiaries within the last three years; or </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Be an executive officer of a company where a KCG director serves on the board of directors. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our N&amp;CG Committee is responsible for determining annually whether each current director is subject to any of the
above factors and reporting to the Board on its determinations. If a director is subject to any of the disqualifying factors or experiences a substantial change in occupation or business association, absent a waiver by a majority of the Board
(excluding the affected director(s)), he or she will immediately offer his or her resignation, which the Board will accept. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_10">
</A>Term Limits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Absent a waiver by a majority of our Board, our Corporate Governance Guidelines limit
directors (other than the CEO) to 15 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> terms on our Board and require that directors resign from the Board effective as of the Board meeting following the date the director reaches 72 years of age.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_11"></A>Director Independence </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To be independent under the rules of the New York Stock Exchange (&#147;NYSE&#148;), our Board must make an affirmative
determination that a director does not have a &#147;material relationship&#148; with KCG (either directly or as a partner, stockholder or officer of an organization that has a material relationship with KCG). The NYSE has bright-line tests that
disqualify a director from being determined to be independent, including if the director is employed by KCG. In addition, the Board must still consider all circumstances surrounding any existing relationship between KCG and a director to determine
whether a material relationship exists outside of the bright-line tests. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Board has considered the
independence of all 13 of our current directors, including through a review of the relationships described under &#147;Our Standards of Independence; Related Party Transactions&#148; below, and has made an affirmative determination that our
independent directors are Charles E. Haldeman, Jr., Debra J. Chrapaty, Peter R. Fisher, Rene M. Kern, James T. Milde, John C. (Hans) Morris, Alastair Rampell, Daniel F. Schmitt, Laurie M. Shahon, Colin Smith, Heather E. Tookes and Adrian Weller. As
our CEO, Daniel Coleman is not independent. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_12"></A>Our Standards of Independence; Related Party Transactions
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Corporate Governance Guidelines require that at least a majority of the directors on our Board be
&#147;independent&#148; as defined under the NYSE Listing Standards. Directors also are required under our Corporate </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-8-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
Governance Guidelines to abide by our Code of Business Conduct and Ethics (a copy of which may be found at our website at <U>www.kcg.com</U> in the &#147;Corporate Governance&#148; section of
&#147;Investors&#148;), and each director must recuse himself or herself from any discussion or decision affecting his or her personal, business or professional interests unrelated to his or her service on the Board. Unless an exception is granted
by a majority vote of our Board and excluding service with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-profit</FONT> institutions, no director may serve on more than two boards of public companies in addition to our Board, and no director may serve on the
board of an entity that has one or more executive officers serving as a member of our Board. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In determining
that each of the directors, other than Mr.&nbsp;Coleman, is independent, our Board reviewed these standards, the corporate governance rules of the NYSE and the SEC, and the individual circumstances of each director. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Code of Business Conduct and Ethics requires all employees to disclose to KCG any conflicts of interest or personal
interests they may have in potential transactions. After full disclosure by an employee, the Company may approve the conduct or transactions at issue in writing. Members of the Board must disclose to the Board any personal interest they may have in
a transaction in which the Board is involved and recuse themselves from participation in any decision in which there is a conflict between their personal interests and the interests of the Company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Additionally, the charter for the Finance and Audit Committee, which we refer to as the &#147;F&amp;A Committee,&#148;
includes a requirement for the F&amp;A Committee to review and approve proposed related party transactions or courses of dealings with respect to which executive officers or directors or members of their immediate families have an interest,
including all transactions with significant stockholders, executive officers, directors or other persons that are required to be disclosed pursuant to Item 404 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K.</FONT> A related party transaction
under Item 404 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K</FONT> is a transaction, arrangement or relationship (or any series of similar transactions, arrangements or relationships) in which KCG was, is or will be a participant and the
amount involved exceeds $120,000 in any fiscal year, and in which any &#147;related party&#148; (defined below) had, has or will have a direct or indirect material interest. The category of related parties consists generally of KCG&#146;s directors,
director nominees, executive officers, any person or entity who is known to be the beneficial owner of more than 5% of any class of KCG voting securities, and immediate family members of any of the foregoing persons. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On April&nbsp;26, 2016, KCG repurchased approximately 1.9&nbsp;million shares of KCG&#146;s Class&nbsp;A common stock,
par value $0.01 per share (&#147;KCG Common Stock&#148;), from former director Daniel Tierney and one of his affiliated entities for $13.48 per share, the closing stock price of KCG Common Stock on the previous date, which represented an aggregate
purchase price of approximately $26.1&nbsp;million. Mr.&nbsp;Tierney was then a holder of more than five percent of the outstanding KCG Common Stock. On that date, KCG also repurchased (i)&nbsp;approximately 2.7&nbsp;million warrants to purchase
shares of KCG Common Stock (&#147;Warrants&#148;) from an entity affiliated with Mr.&nbsp;Tierney for approximately $5.9&nbsp;million and (ii)&nbsp;approximately 3.8&nbsp;million Warrants from entities affiliated with former director Stephen Schuler
for approximately $8.3&nbsp;million. Mr.&nbsp;Schuler&#146;s service on the Board expired upon the election of directors at the 2016 Annual Meeting of Stockholders on May&nbsp;11, 2016. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On November&nbsp;17, 2016, KCG entered into a purchase agreement (the &#147;Purchase Agreement&#148;) with <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO</FONT> Interholdco, LLC <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(&#147;GA-GTCO&#148;),</FONT> an affiliate of General Atlantic, LLC (&#147;General Atlantic&#148;) and, at the time, a holder of approximately 22% of the
outstanding shares of KCG Common Stock who, in connection with the closing of the Mergers, appointed two directors to KCG&#146;s Board (Rene M. Kern, a managing director of General Atlantic, and John C. (Hans) Morris, a former employee of General
Atlantic). Pursuant to the terms of the Purchase Agreement, KCG exchanged approximately 8.9&nbsp;million shares of common stock of Bats, par value $0.01 per share (&#147;Bats Common Stock&#148;) held by a subsidiary of KCG, for approximately
18.7&nbsp;million shares of KCG Common Stock and approximately 8.1&nbsp;million Warrants held by <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO,</FONT> which constituted all of the KCG Common Stock and Warrants held by
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO</FONT> (collectively, the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;GA-GTCO</FONT> Transaction&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Jefferies LLC (together with certain of its affiliates, &#147;Jefferies&#148;), a holder of approximately 24% of the outstanding KCG Common Stock (including restricted stock units), was paid transaction
fees of $2.9&nbsp;million for </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-9-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
acting as broker and for advisory activities associated with the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO</FONT> Transaction, half of which was payable by KCG and the other half of which was
payable by <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO.</FONT> KCG paid the entire $2.9&nbsp;million fee to Jefferies in cash and, pursuant to the terms of the Purchase Agreement, retained 46,495 shares of Bats Common Stock that were otherwise
transferable to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO</FONT> pursuant to the Purchase Agreement, which had a fair market value as of the date of the Purchase Agreement equal to the fees payable by <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">GA-GTCO</FONT>
to Jefferies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On November&nbsp;18, 2016, KCG sold 2,174,654 shares of Bats Common Stock to Jefferies in a
block trade transaction for $30.35 per share. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In 2016, KCG earned revenues of $14,113,447 from Jefferies
related to KCG&#146;s ordinary course trading relationships with Jefferies, a significant portion of which related to expenses incurred by KCG in connection with trades executed on behalf of Jefferies, which amounts were initially paid to KCG by
Jefferies (and therefore included in revenues earned from Jefferies), but subsequently paid by KCG to third parties in respect of such trading expenses. In addition, in 2016, KCG made payments of $856,530 to Jefferies related to KCG&#146;s ordinary
course trading relationships with Jefferies. This ordinary course trading relationship with Jefferies began prior to the time that it became a beneficial owner of more than five percent of the common stock of Knight, a predecessor to KCG.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_13"></A>BOARD OVERSIGHT OF RISK </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Successful management of the Company requires identifying, monitoring and managing risk. Risk oversight begins with the
Board of Directors and two key Board committees: the Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee and the F&amp;A Committee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On July&nbsp;20, 2016, the Company&#146;s Risk Committee was changed to the Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee. In addition to identifying, monitoring and assessing the key risks of the Company, the
Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee monitors major technology related strategies, projects and technology architecture of the Company, including those relating to cybersecurity and information security and technology. The Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology
Committee meets at least on a quarterly basis to review and assess our risks, control processes with respect to such risks, and our major technology related strategies and projects. The Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee meets at least annually
with our F&amp;A Committee (and met four times in 2016) to discuss matters relating to the overlap between risk and internal control functions. As set forth in our Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee&#146;s Charter, our Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology
Committee&#146;s responsibilities include, among others: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To review and discuss with management the Company&#146;s organizational risk governance approach to risk management and its methods for identifying
and managing risks; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Except for functions performed by the F&amp;A Committee (i.e., financial risk exposure, including the liquidity risk management policy), to review
and discuss with management the Company&#146;s risk appetite and tolerance and key risks, including credit risk, market risk, operational risk (including but not limited to technology risk) and reputational risk, in the context of the Company&#146;s
business strategy, financial resources and performance; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To review and discuss with the Company&#146;s Chief Risk Officer, the Company&#146;s risk assessment and risk management guidelines, controls,
policies and processes, as the case may be. The Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee will meet separately at least twice a year with the Company&#146;s Chief Risk Officer; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

framework to prevent, detect and respond to cyber-attacks or breaches, and to review significant new and existing information technology and cybersecurity risk exposures and the steps management has taken to monitor and control such exposures;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In coordination with the F&amp;A Committee, to review and discuss disclosures regarding risk contained in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> and certain other securities filings, as appropriate; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To review reports on selected risk topics as the Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee deems appropriate from time to time;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To discharge any other duties or responsibilities delegated to the Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee by the Board; and
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To receive, as and when appropriate, reports from the Company&#146;s internal audit group on the results of risk management reviews and assessments.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Board&#146;s F&amp;A Committee also plays a role in risk oversight. Our F&amp;A
Committee has oversight responsibility for the integrity of the Company&#146;s financial statements and its risk and control environment, the relationship with the Company&#146;s independent auditor and the Company&#146;s internal audit function. At
the management level, the internal audit function is responsible for providing reliable and timely information to our Board and management regarding the Company&#146;s effectiveness in identifying and appropriately controlling risks. The F&amp;A
Committee meets periodically with our Chief Executive Officer, our Chief Financial Officer, our General Counsel, our Chief Risk Officer, our Director of Internal Audit and the Company&#146;s independent auditor in separate private sessions to
discuss any matters that may warrant committee attention. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The F&amp;A Committee consists of independent
directors who meet the independence, experience and financial literacy requirements of The Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 (the &#147;SOX Act&#148;), the NYSE and applicable rules of the SEC. In addition, at least one member of the F&amp;A Committee must
be an audit committee financial expert under SEC rules (or the F&amp;A Committee will advise the Company that none of its members so qualifies). The Board has determined that Mr.&nbsp;Schmitt is an audit committee financial expert. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company&#146;s independent auditor reports directly to the F&amp;A Committee, which has the sole authority to appoint
or replace the independent auditor and to approve all audit engagement fees and terms and all permitted <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> engagements. The F&amp;A Committee also has the sole authority to hire and replace the
Company&#146;s Director of Internal Audit. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The following responsibilities, among other things, are within the
authority of the F&amp;A Committee: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Periodically discuss with management, at least annually, the Company&#146;s major financial risk and fraud risk exposures, and the steps management
has taken to monitor and control such exposures, including the Company&#146;s risk assessment and risk management policies; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Discuss with the independent auditor, the Director of Internal Audit and senior management as appropriate: (i)&nbsp;the adequacy of the
Company&#146;s internal controls, including significant deficiencies in the design or operation of internal controls which could adversely affect the Company&#146;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial data, and
management&#146;s response and (ii)&nbsp;any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Review the yearly report prepared by management and attested to by the Company&#146;s independent auditor, assessing the effectiveness of the
Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting and stating management&#146;s responsibility for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting prior to its inclusion in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on
Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K.</FONT> Receive a report from management of all significant deficiencies and/or material weaknesses and their disposition; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-11-
</FONT></P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Review and approve procedures for receipt, retention and treatment of complaints regarding accounting, internal accounting controls or auditing
matters, including confidential anonymous submissions by employees. Annually review procedures for effectiveness. All significant matters received and their proposed resolution must be reported to and discussed with the F&amp;A Committee; and
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Review the Company&#146;s disclosure control procedures in accordance with Section&nbsp;302 of the SOX Act and monitor that they are followed in
preparation of quarterly and annual financial statements. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our primary risk exposures
(including those relating to cybersecurity risk), as well as our risk management framework and methodologies, are discussed in further detail on pages 50 to 54 in our Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year
ended December&nbsp;31, 2016. See &#147;Compensation and Risk&#148; on page 19 below for a discussion of risk assessment as it relates to our compensation program. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_14"></A>BOARD MEETINGS AND BOARD COMMITTEE INFORMATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_15">
</A>Board Meetings </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Each member of our current Board of Directors was elected by stockholders at the 2016
Annual Meeting, other than Messrs. Fisher, Smith and Weller and Ms.&nbsp;Tookes, who were elected to the Board of Directors on January&nbsp;18, 2017. Rene M. Kern and John C. (Hans) Morris, current members of our Board, are not seeking <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> to the Board, and their respective terms will expire upon the election of directors at the Annual Meeting, at which time the Board will be reduced to 11 members. Our Board held nine meetings in 2016. Our
Corporate Governance Guidelines provide that our directors are expected to attend all regular and special meetings of our Board and committees on which they sit. For 2016, each director attended at least 75% of the aggregate number of meetings of
our Board and of the committees on which he or she was a member during the time that he or she was a director, except for Mr.&nbsp;Kern, who attended less than 75% of the meetings due to being recused from one meeting of our Board concerning matters
in which he had an interest as a managing director of General Atlantic. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_16"></A>Committees and Committee Charters
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Board has established several standing committees, including the F&amp;A Committee, the N&amp;CG
Committee, the Compensation Committee and the Risk&nbsp;&amp; Technology Committee. Each of the committees makes recommendations to our Board as appropriate and reports periodically to the entire Board. The charters of each committee are available
on our website in the &#147;Corporate Governance&#148; section of &#147;Investors.&#148; </FONT></P>
