<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(1)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Audit Fees represent the aggregate fees for professional services rendered for the audit of KCG&#146;s annual financial statements for the
applicable year and reviews of KCG&#146;s financial statements included in SEC Forms <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q</FONT> during the applicable year. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Tax Fees represent fees paid in the applicable year for assistance with domestic and international income tax compliance, tax examinations and
general tax advice. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other Fees is primarily comprised of fees relating to XBRL tagging of financial statements. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_75"></A><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">PRE-APPROVAL</FONT> POLICY FOR
AUDIT AND <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">NON-AUDIT</FONT> SERVICES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our F&amp;A Committee is responsible
for appointing, setting compensation for and overseeing the work of the independent registered public accounting firm. In addition, our F&amp;A Committee is responsible for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approving</FONT> permitted <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services and fees to be performed by the independent registered public accounting firm and determine that such services are compatible with maintaining its independence. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On an ongoing basis, our management communicates specific projects and categories of service for which the advance
approval of the F&amp;A Committee is requested. The F&amp;A Committee reviews these requests and advises management if the F&amp;A Committee approves the engagement of the independent registered public accounting firm. The F&amp;A Committee may
delegate to one or more of its members the authority to grant <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> required by this policy. On a periodic basis, our management reports to the F&amp;A Committee regarding the actual spending for such
projects and services compared to the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> amounts. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In
granting <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> of certain <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services for 2016, the F&amp;A Committee considered whether the provision of such
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services rendered by our independent registered public accounting firm was compatible with maintaining their objectivity and independence. The F&amp;A Committee concluded that such objectivity and
independence would be maintained. For 2016, all of the fees associated with the independent registered public accounting firm services were <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> by the F&amp;A Committee. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-55-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_76"></A>INFORMATION ON STOCK OWNERSHIP </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_76a"></A>BENEFICIAL OWNERSHIP OF DIRECTORS, EXECUTIVE OFFICERS AND HOLDERS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>OF 5% OR MORE OF OUTSTANDING STOCK </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The following table sets forth, as of March 24, 2017 certain information regarding the beneficial ownership of the KCG Common Stock by: (i)&nbsp;each of KCG&#146;s named executive officers; (ii)&nbsp;each
KCG director; (iii)&nbsp;each person who is known to KCG to own beneficially more than 5% of the KCG Common Stock; and (iv)&nbsp;the current executive officers and directors of KCG as a group. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Such information is based, in part, upon information provided by certain stockholders of KCG. In the case of persons
other than the current executive officers and directors of KCG, such information is based on a review of Forms 4, Schedules 13D and 13G filed with the SEC and information provided by the relevant persons. As of March 24, 2017, there were 124 holders
of record of KCG Common Stock and approximately 13,866 beneficial holders of KCG Common Stock. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_77"></A>SECTION 16(A) BENEFICIAL OWNERSHIP REPORTING COMPLIANCE
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Section 16(a) of the Exchange Act requires our directors and executive officers and any beneficial owner
of more than 10% of any class of our equity securities to file with the SEC initial reports of beneficial ownership and reports of changes in ownership of any of our securities. These reports are made on documents referred to as Forms 3, 4 and 5.
Our directors and executive officers must also provide us with copies of these reports. We have reviewed the copies of the reports that we have received and written representations from the individuals required to file the reports. Based on this
review, we believe that during 2016 each of our directors and executive officers timely complied with applicable reporting requirements for transactions in our equity securities. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-58-
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_78"></A>ANNUAL MEETING INFORMATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Board of Directors is soliciting your proxy for our 2017 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and any adjournment of the
meeting, for the purposes set forth in the Notice of Annual Meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_79"></A>Notice and Access of Proxy Materials
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To expedite delivery, reduce our costs and decrease the environmental impact of our proxy materials, we
have elected, in accordance with the SEC&#146;s &#147;Notice and Access&#148; rule, to deliver the Notice to our stockholders and to provide proxy materials to our stockholders over the Internet. The Notice is being mailed on March&nbsp;31, 2017 to
all of our stockholders who have not requested a paper or electronic copy of our proxy materials. This Proxy Statement and our 2016 Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> will first be made available to our stockholders
on or about that date. If you received a Notice, you will not receive a printed copy of the proxy materials in the mail. Instead, the Notice instructs you on how to access and review all of the important information contained in the proxy materials
and how to submit your proxy via the Internet or by mail. If you received a Notice and would like to receive a copy of our proxy materials, follow the instructions contained in the Notice to obtain a copy electronically or request a copy in paper
form, which will include a proxy card or voting instruction form, on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-time</FONT> or ongoing basis at no charge. We will not mail a paper copy of the Proxy Statement and Annual Report to you unless specifically
requested to do so. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_80"></A>Who Can Vote; Outstanding Shares on Record Date </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Only stockholders of record of the KCG Common Stock at the close of business on March&nbsp;14, 2017, which we refer to as
the &#147;record date,&#148; may vote at the Annual Meeting. On the record date, we had 62,660,624 shares of KCG Common Stock outstanding (excluding (i)&nbsp;RSUs, which do not have voting rights, (ii)&nbsp;KCG Common Stock held in our treasury and
(iii)&nbsp;outstanding warrants to purchase KCG Common Stock). You are entitled to one vote for each share of KCG Common Stock that you owned on the record date. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_81"></A>What Is a Proxy? </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your proxy
gives us authority to vote your shares and tells us how to vote your shares at the Annual Meeting or any adjournment. Two of our employees, who are called &#147;proxies&#148; or &#147;proxy holders&#148; and are named on the proxy card, will vote
your shares at the Annual Meeting according to the instructions you give on the proxy card or by telephone or over the Internet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_82">
</A>Voting Your Shares; Revoking Your Proxy </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your vote is important. Whether or not you plan to attend the
Annual Meeting, we encourage you to vote your shares promptly. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You may vote in any of the following four
ways: (i)&nbsp;by attending the Annual Meeting; (ii)&nbsp;by calling the toll-free telephone number listed on the proxy card; (iii)&nbsp;by voting on the Internet at the website address listed on the Notice or proxy card; or (iv)&nbsp;if you
requested a paper copy of this Proxy Statement, by marking, signing, dating and mailing your proxy card in the postage-paid envelope provided or return it to Vote Processing, c/o Broadridge, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York 11717. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-59-
</FONT></P>

a proxy properly signed and received at or before the Annual Meeting, unless subsequently properly revoked, will be voted in accordance with the instructions indicated therein. If a proxy is signed and returned without indicating any voting
instructions for any particular matter or matters, shares of KCG Common Stock represented by such proxy will be voted as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

Annual Meeting other than as described herein. If, however, other matters are properly brought before the Annual Meeting or any adjournments or postponements thereof, the persons appointed as proxies will have the discretion to vote or act thereon
in accordance with their best judgment, unless authority to do so is withheld in the proxy. Any proxy given pursuant to this solicitation may be revoked by the person giving it at any time before the shares of KCG Common Stock represented by such
proxy are voted at the Annual Meeting by: (i)&nbsp;attending and voting in person at the Annual Meeting; (ii)&nbsp;giving notice of revocation of the proxy at the Annual Meeting; (iii)&nbsp;submitting a proxy relating to the same shares and matters
to be considered at the Annual Meeting (by telephone, by Internet or by submitting a paper proxy card) on a later date than the proxy previously submitted or (iv)&nbsp;delivering a written notice of revocation to the Corporate Secretary of KCG.
Attendance at the Annual Meeting will not in and of itself constitute a revocation of a proxy. All written notices of revocation and other communications with respect to the revocation of proxies should be addressed as follows: KCG Holdings, Inc.,
300 Vesey Street, New York, NY 10282, Attention: Corporate Secretary, and must be received before the taking of the votes at the Annual Meeting. If you own shares of KCG Common Stock held in street name and wish to vote at the Annual Meeting, you
must have a legal proxy from your broker. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_83"></A>Annual Meeting Admission </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All stockholders will need to present photo identification to be admitted into the Annual Meeting. Beneficial owners of
stock held by banks, brokers or investment plans (in &#147;street name&#148;) will also need proof of ownership. A recent brokerage statement or letter or legal proxy from your broker or bank are examples of proof of ownership. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_84"></A>Quorum </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A quorum is the minimum number of shares required to conduct business at the Annual Meeting. Under our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws,</FONT> to have a quorum, a majority of the issued and
outstanding shares of stock entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting must be represented in person or by proxy at the meeting. Shares of KCG Common Stock represented by proxies that are marked &#147;Abstain&#148; and broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> will be counted as shares of KCG Common Stock present for purposes of determining the presence of a quorum on all matters, but will not, unless otherwise noted herein, be counted as votes cast in favor of
the matters brought before the stockholders at the Annual Meeting. In the event a quorum is not present at the Annual Meeting, we expect that the Annual Meeting will be adjourned or postponed to solicit additional proxies. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-60-

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If your shares are held through a broker, the broker will ask you how you want your
shares to be voted. If you give the broker instructions, your shares will be voted as you direct. If you do not give instructions, pursuant to NYSE rules, if you own your shares of KCG Common Stock through a broker and you do not vote, your broker
may vote your shares of KCG Common Stock at its discretion on certain &#147;routine&#148; matters. KCG believes that all of the matters to be voted upon at the Annual Meeting, except for the ratification of the appointment of PwC as KCG&#146;s
independent registered public accounting firm for 2017, are not considered &#147;routine&#148; matters under NYSE rules, and therefore, brokers will not be permitted to vote, at their discretion, any unvoted shares on those proposals (reported as a
broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote).</FONT> </FONT></P>

to be voted upon at the Annual Meeting, and the effect of each such choice: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Voting Options</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Effect&nbsp;of&nbsp;Abstentions</B></FONT></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If the Annual Meeting were to be postponed or adjourned, your proxy would still be valid and may be voted at the postponed
or adjourned meeting in the manner described in this Proxy Statement. You would still be able to revoke your proxy until it was voted. </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_87"></A>OTHER INFORMATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_88"></A>Stockholder Proposals for 2018 Annual Meeting </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In accordance with KCG&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws,</FONT> stockholder proposals intended to be
presented at KCG&#146;s 2018 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and stockholder nominations for election to the Board must be received by KCG not less than 90 and not more than 120 days prior to the anniversary date of the 2017 Annual Meeting, or after
January&nbsp;10, 2018 but before February&nbsp;9, 2018. Such proposals and nominations must be delivered to, or mailed to and received by, the Corporate Secretary for KCG at 300 Vesey Street, New York, NY 10282, or at such other address as KCG
indicates thereafter and must otherwise meet the requirements as described in KCG&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws.</FONT> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Stockholder proposals must be in proper form and meet the requirements specified in our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws.</FONT> For example, a stockholder&#146;s notice with respect to a
nomination for election to the Board must include, among other things: (i)&nbsp;the name, age, business address and residence of the person the stockholder proposes to nominate for election as a director; (ii)&nbsp;the principal occupation or
employment of the person; (iii)&nbsp;the class or series and number of shares of capital stock of KCG which are owned beneficially or of record by the person; (iv)&nbsp;a description of all direct and indirect compensation and other material
monetary agreements, arrangements and understandings during the past three years, and any other material relationships, between or among such stockholder and beneficial owner, if any, and their respective affiliates and associates, or others acting
in concert therewith, on the one hand, and each proposed nominee, and his or her respective affiliates and associates, or others acting in concert therewith, on the other hand; (v)&nbsp;any other information relating to the person that would be
required to be made in connection with solicitations of proxies for election of directors pursuant to Section&nbsp;14 of the Exchange Act and the rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; and (vi)&nbsp;certain information about the nominating
stockholder, as specified in our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">By-Laws.</FONT> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Additionally, applicable
SEC rules and regulations govern the submission of stockholder proposals and KCG&#146;s consideration of them for inclusion in the annual meeting proxy statement and form of proxy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_89"></A>How Our Board Solicits Proxies; Expenses of Solicitation </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">KCG will bear the entire cost of the solicitation of proxies and the cost of printing and mailing this Proxy Statement. KCG has retained the services of Okapi Partners LLC (&#147;Okapi&#148;) to assist in
the solicitation of proxies. Okapi will receive a fee from KCG for services rendered of approximately $6,500, plus reimbursement for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses. In addition
to solicitation by mail, the directors, officers and employees of KCG may solicit proxies from stockholders of KCG by telephone, electronic communication or by personal interview. Such directors, officers and employees will not be additionally
compensated for any such solicitation but may be reimbursed for reasonable <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses in connection therewith. Arrangements may also be made with brokers,
custodians, nominees and fiduciaries for the forwarding of solicitation material to the beneficial owners of shares of KCG Common Stock held of record by such persons and KCG will reimburse such brokers, custodians, nominees and fiduciaries for
their reasonable <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses in connection therewith. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You can save KCG additional expense and further reduce the environmental impact of delivering paper proxy materials to stockholders by electing to receive future proxy statements and annual reports
electronically. If you would like to request this electronic delivery, please follow the instructions on the proxy card to vote using the internet and, when prompted, indicate that you agree to receive or access proxy materials electronically in
future years. If you elected to receive proxy materials electronically over the Internet and would now like to receive a paper copy of the proxy materials so that you may submit a paper proxy in lieu of an electronic proxy, you may request a paper
copy (i)&nbsp;by Internet at www.proxyvote.com, (ii)&nbsp;by telephone at <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-800-579-1639</FONT></FONT></FONT> or (iii)&nbsp;by sending an <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail</FONT> to sendmaterial@proxyvote.com. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_90"></A>Householding </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The SEC has adopted rules that permit companies and intermediaries such as brokers to satisfy delivery requirements for
proxy statements, notices of internet availability of proxy statements and annual reports with </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-63-
</FONT></P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
respect to two or more stockholders sharing the same address by delivering a single proxy statement, notice of internet availability of proxy statement or annual report, as applicable, addressed
to those stockholders. We have delivered only one Notice or set of proxy materials to multiple stockholders who share that address unless we received contrary instructions from any stockholder at that address. This process, which is commonly
referred to as &#147;householding,&#148; potentially provides extra convenience for stockholders and cost savings for companies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If your household received (i)&nbsp;a single copy of the Notice or proxy materials this year, but you would like to receive a separate copy this year and/or in the future, or (ii)&nbsp;multiple copies of
the Notice or proxy materials this year, but you would like to receive a single copy in the future, please notify your broker if your shares are held in a brokerage account, or us if you are the record holder of your shares. You can notify us by
sending a written request to Broadridge Financial Solutions, Householding Department, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, NY 11717 or by calling
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-866-540-7095.</FONT></FONT></FONT> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="toc322410_91">
</A>Other Business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Management of KCG knows of no other matters that may properly be, or which are likely
to be, brought before the Annual Meeting. However, if any other matters are properly brought before such Annual Meeting, the persons named in the enclosed proxy or their substitutes intend to vote the proxies in accordance with their judgment with
respect to such matters, unless authority to do so is withheld in the proxy. </FONT></P>

hereby authorize(s) them to represent and to vote, as designated on the reverse side of this ballot, all of the shares of common stock of KCG HOLDINGS, INC. that the stockholder(s) is/are entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be
held at 1:00 PM EDT on May&nbsp;10, 2017, at 300 Vesey Street, New York, NY 10282, and any adjournment or postponement thereof.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
